description:
A tribute to Criola, a Brazilian performer and graffiti writer from Belo Horizonte. Embracing the roots of Brazil, she brings a powerful geometric work that inspired us to create a piece celebrating all women who enhance culture and diversity in art. 

"Tinta é poder" means Paint is Power. When we have the art materials to express ourselves, we can share experiences and value our identities, reaching people. Expression is Power, express yourself.

